    "In particular, topology-aware loss has demonstrated considerable success in maintaining fossil boundaries, where traditional crossentropy loss often falls short.",
    "Despite the progress made, generalizing segmentation models across diverse fossil datasets remains a significant challenge.",
    "While models perform well on the data they are trained on, their effectiveness diminishes when applied to fossils subjected to different geological or environmental conditions.",
    "This limitation underscores the need for ongoing research into model generalization and robustness, with a focus on developing architectures and training strategies that can better handle the variability inherent in the fossil record.",
    "This section introduces new ideas for fossil image analysis, building on the strengths and limitations of current methods."
